#!/usr/bin/env sh
# entwurf pre-commit gate.
#
# `pnpm check` is the entire static-quality surface: biome check, the 3-config
# tsc fence, and every deterministic check-*/smoke-* gate wired into
# package.json's `check` chain (run.sh usage documents each one). That chain is
# the SSOT — this comment deliberately does NOT enumerate it, because a
# hand-copied list here rotted once already (it named five 0.4-era gates that
# no longer exist). The hook just wires the SSOT in. Anything beyond it —
# LIVE smokes, release-gate — stays explicit; those need real backends.
#
# Bypass with `git commit --no-verify` only when you genuinely understand
# why the gate complained — the typical answer is "fix the underlying
# issue, not the hook".

pnpm check
